latestIgtvVideos.title: updated skincare routine ✨(current favourite products)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
here’s my current quick morning skincare routine. 
i haven’t posted one in a while and i thought showing you the products i’ve incorporated lately and how i’ve been loving them could also be another way of putting this post up.

i’ve been enjoying:
•the @laneigeindia cream skin refiner.
•the @vauntskincare multivitamin hydrator (serum)
•the @biodermaindia atoderm intensive baume.
•lastly @theearthrhythm ultra defence sunscreen.
i’m still stuck with the @mcaffeineofficial eye cream cause i still haven’t figured an eye cream/serum that really works (i mean you can tell from the packaging)
also used the @neutrogena spf 15 lip moisturiser.
i broke out here and there lately and the dark spots are slowly fading ✨

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
it’s been a while since i posted anything ever since i was bitten by a dog badly. exactly one week from what happened and i decided to do a quick, simple, morning skincare routine. i just wanted to finally be able to be in front of the camera talking to you guys and doing what i love. i want to thank friends and followers for the love and support, it was what stripped away the discouraging feels i had. 
also, i know y’all might think beauty bloggers and other bloggers are always nagging about pushing their post and engaging but we need it ✨
i took a break and the engagement has gone down and would love for you guys to throw that love and support like confetti 🤍 ily guys ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: my first niacinamide!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
this could be a day routine if you end it with an spf but i usually use my niacinamide at night. 
i hope you guys enjoy these routines as much as the makeup videos because there’s no makeup if there’s no skincare for me. i’m sure you feel the same way :’) 
*i’ll review this niacinamide serum from @theearthrhythm in less than two months. for now my skin does not react, it feels nice on the skin but note this that ‘NIACINAMIDE’ shouldn’t be used with ‘VITAMIN C’ especially if you’re of a sensitive skin type because these two products create niacin (a yellow solution) that can tingle your skin turning yellow and even cause rashes or breakouts*
